<br>
That, in my experience, is not quite the case. I am an untwinked level 47 Monk in a small under-50 guild, although some of our toons are second and third characters. My guild leader is a 47 Warrior whose previous main was a 58 Mage. Granted, I have spent most of the last 17 levels in Crystal Caverns and have about 20+K worth of gear, including a Tink bag, but he has, for the most part, better armor.<br>
<br>
The end result? Buffed with level-appropriate Clerical buffs, I have 1,030 AC (Defense only 222) and he is nowhere close to 1,000AC. With maxed Defense and wielding my AC weapons, I would be around 1050+.<br>
<br>
If I go to DL and group low blues, I can easily tank unslowed mobs in a chain-pulling 3-person group with a Druid and a Cleric. With slows, it's a joke. And yes, I get missed a lot and when I do get hit, I tend to get hit for max more than plate classes, but not enough to make me a bad tank. I do prefer to have plate classes in the group, but it's by no means necessary.<br>
<br>
Is it fair? I don't know. I suspect that it is at least somewhat unbalancing, although it sure makes forming groups easier. Since I can function as a MT and as a damage dealer at the same time, we can add more classes as they become available instead of waiting for a tank and a damage dealer to show up. Still, I can see why my guild leader is a little jealous of my AC. Good thing he is a great guy or else he would have probably made luggage out of my tail a long time ago <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Admittedly, things change some if the group needs to fight high blues or higher. Introduce me to a level 44-45 Greater War Boned Skeleton or a level 43-46 Forest Giant Ancient, and I get uncomfortable. Still doable, though, unless I lose agro and can't get it back because I don't have Taunt. Of course, I'd never dream of tanking on raids, but then there are usually higher level tanks available there anyway.<br>
<br>
So I guess my question is: Is this change going to affect moderately equipped Monks tanking LOW blues solo or in groups? Will it make tanking HIGH blues totally impossible? Or will it only affect the Monks who can tank on raids, ubers, etc? I don't think we know the answer to that, although it sounds like what they currently have running on Test is not going to change the whole &quot;Monks tanking low blues&quot; thing.<br>
<br>
