<br>
I really urge Verant to go and review the resistance items that can be _reasonably_ attained by monks (of all levels), and what attaining those resistances does to possible HP and AC of the monk.  Resists have always been a problem for monks - I have played many class in the last 3 years, and the others never really had to consider resists, they just happenned, with my monk I have to work hard on them.  That was pre-patch, now I cannot imagine how I will ever achieve 100 to all resists without being in an uber guild.  Currently my monk has aroun 50 in all resists and that _includes_ the resists on my epic - AC 1050, HP around 2100.<br>
<br>
I for one am totally fed up with insta chain casting wizards perma stunning/rooting/ice cometing my monk on a pull.  The damn casters dont stop til they are oom, and unlike PCs, dont have any form of pause between casting to allow, say, an FD.  Look at my hp, not unusual for a 58 monk really - yet that is around 2 ice comets worth of hp...<br>
<br>
Now, I gotta worry about getting even more AC too so I can be beaten to a pulp when tanking as I do now?  I really don't know where all this monk tanking thing comes from.  At 58 I cannot solo anything without using both stonestance and mend, so thats around 1 mob every 6 minutes?  Tanking, I tried that in seb the other day cause we couldn't get real PLATE class tank who could take the hits.  And while I managed it, I was a mana sponge - oh AND I was puller, so I had the double jeapordy (sp?) of mis-timed heals on a low a HP monk and and getting ice cometted to death on the pull.<br>
<br>
/sigh<br>
